entries.description: A governance proxy that lets eth:0x4e4943346848c4867F81dFb37c4cA9C5715A7828 act through it.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: create new zk chains (based on the current version), register tokens (ZK cluster Admin role).
revert batches for any connected chain (ZK cluster Admin role).

upgradeTimestamps.description: Timestamps for new protocol version upgrades can be registered here (NOT enforced)

entries.name: BridgeHub
entries.description: The main registry (hub) for all the contracts in the ZK stack cluster and central entrypoint for bridge transactions. Stores important mappings like from chainId to diamond address, from chainId to parent CTM, from chainId to base token etc. A clone of Bridgehub is also deployed on each L2 chain, but this clone is only used on settlement layers.

chainsCreated.description: All new chains created go thorugh the central bridgehub and are stored here with their respective STMs.

settlementLayers.description: New settlement layers and their whitelist status. Chains can be migrated to whitelisted settlement layers by their chain admin.

entries.name: L1GenesisUpgrade
entries.description: Diamond implementation code to initialize new ZK chains. Used to set their chainID.

receivedPermissions.description: create new zk chains (based on the current version), register tokens (ZK cluster Admin role).
revert batches for any connected chain (ZK cluster Admin role).

entries.name: MessageRoot
entries.description: Aggregates remote bridge message roots from all ZK stack chains. To be used with the Gateway when deployed.

entries.name: Guardians
entries.description: Custom Multisig implementation that has a general threshold of 5 and a specific threshold for extending the legal voting period of 2.

receivedPermissions.description: extend the legal veto period, approve a protocol upgrade.
one of its 3/3 signers.

entries.name: CTMDeploymentTracker
entries.description: Asset deployment tracker where the 'asset' is a ChainTypeManager. The registering of asset IDs for ChainTypeManagers is necessary to be able to migrate them to a given settlement layer, for example the Gateway.

entries.name: SecurityCouncil
entries.description: Custom Multisig implementation that has a general threshold of 9 but also specific thresholds for upgrade approvals (6) or soft freezes (3).

receivedPermissions.description: soft freeze, hard freeze, approve a protocol upgrade.
one of its 3/3 signers.

softFreezeNonce.description: Increments with each softFreeze (freezes ALL Hyperchains (blocks Mailbox and Executor facets) connected to the main STM for SOFT_FREEZE_PERIOD

hardFreezeNonce.description: Increments with each hardFreeze (freezes ALL Hyperchains (blocks Mailbox and Executor facets) connected to the main STM for HARD_FREEZE_PERIOD

references.text: Security Council members - ZK Nation docs

entries.name: RollupL1DAValidator
entries.description: Contract that verifies the data availability of ethereum calldata and blobs. Can be used by ZK stack rollups as the L1 part of a DAValidator pair.

entries.name: L1AssetRouter
entries.description: Part of the v26 upgrade: Canonical central asset router for all ZK stack chains (not escrowing funds).

receivedPermissions.description: one of its 3/3 signers.

entries.name: L1NativeTokenVault
entries.description: Canonical central asset escrow for all ZK stack chains.

entries.name: ChainTypeManager
entries.description: Defines L2 diamond contract versions, creation and upgrade data and the proof system for all ZK stack chains connected to it. ZK chains are children of this central contract and can only upgrade to versions that were previously registered here. The current protocol version is 0,29,2.

entries.name: L1Nullifier
entries.description: Contract responsible for bookkeeping L1 bridging transactions. Used to finalize withdrawals and reclaim failed deposits. Does not escrow funds.

entries.name: ChainAssetHandler
entries.description: Specialized contract for managing chain assets, i.e. chain migrations.

paused.description: this 'paused' is unrelated to migrations and only used for initialization.

migrations.description: zk chain migrations that were started

entries.name: ProtocolUpgradeHandler
entries.description: The central upgrade contract and Governance proxy for all ZK stack contracts. Accepts successful DAO proposals from L2 and emergency proposals from the EmergencyUpgradeBoard. The three members of the EmergencyUpgradeBoard also have special roles and permissions in this contract.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: set critical contract addresses for the shared cluster, register settlement layers, pause and unpause migrations and the bridge and manage zk chain registration.

manage the shared ValidatorTimelock contract address and the admin role, register and execute upgrades (and set their deadlines), freeze, revert batches and set permissioned validators and fee params for all connected chains.
pause, unpause and set critical escrow address references.
manage allowed rollup DA pairs (allowed to be used by rollups in permanent rollup mode).

protocolFrozenUntil.description: Timestamp until which ALL Hyperchains connected to the main STM are frozen. (Mailbox and Executor facets blocked)

entries.name: RollupDAManager
entries.description: Simple registry for allowed DA address pairs for the 'rollup' data availability mode (can be permanently enforced with isPermanentRollup=true). Rollup DA address pairs (especially the L1 part) usually point to contracts that validate if data was made available on Ethereum.

entries.name: EmergencyUpgradeBoard
entries.description: A custom contract allowing a 3/3 of eth:0x66E4431266DC7E04E7d8b7FE9d2181253df7F410, eth:0xbC1653bd3829dfEc575AfC3816D4899cd103B51c and eth:0x600dA620Ab29F41ABC6596a15981e14cE58c86b8 to `executeEmergencyUpgrade()` via the eth:0xE30Dca3047B37dc7d88849dE4A4Dc07937ad5Ab3.

entries.name: ServerNotifier
entries.description: A simple contract that can be called by the ChainAdmin to emit notifications about chain migrations.

entries.name: ZkProtocolGovernor
entries.description: Main Governance contract allowing for token voting (simple majority) with the ZK token through delegates. This contract is used for protocol upgrade proposals (ZIPs) that start on ZKsync Era, go through Ethereum Layer 1 and can - from there - target all L1 and L2 contracts. At least 21M ZK tokens are necessary to start a proposal and a 630M quorum of voted tokens must be met to succeed.

This contract is used for Token Program Proposals (TPPs) usually targeting the ZK token on ZKsync Era. At least 21M ZK tokens are necessary to start a proposal (for delegates) and a 630M quorum of voted tokens must be met to succeed.
